claim.claim-text:
6. A method for training a player of a game in which an object is projected sequentially towards the player at first, second and third velocity ranges to increase the ocular focus of the player, the method being performed in a single training session and comprising the steps of: 
providing an apparatus for projecting a plurality of objects one at a time towards the player and for varying the velocity of a projected object and; 
projecting a first quantity of the plurality of objects one at a time towards the player at a first velocity; 
after projecting the first quantity of objects one at a time towards the player at the first velocity, projecting a second quantity of the plurality of objects one at a time towards the player at a second velocity greater than the first velocity to increase the players ocular focus at the second velocity; and 
after projecting the second quantity of objects one at a time towards the player at the second velocity, projecting a third quantity of the plurality of objects one at a time towards the player at a third velocity less than the second velocity.
